      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 93: `_xml_escape` escapes quotes and apostrophes in element text, but ElementTree/lupdate do not require those in text nodes. This creates non-canonical diffs despite the comment saying it matches `lupdate`, and may cause churn on the next `lupdate` run. Escape only `\u0026`, `\u003c`, and `\u003e` for element content.\n```suggestion\n    return (text.replace(\u0027\u0026\u0027, \u0027\u0026amp;\u0027)\n                .replace(\u0027\u003c\u0027, \u0027\u0026lt;\u0027)\n                .replace(\u0027\u003e\u0027, \u0027\u0026gt;\u0027))\n```",
