      "message": "[Critical] Line 124: Translations are keyed only by `(context, source)`, but Qt TS messages can have the same context/source with different `\u003ccomment\u003e` disambiguation, IDs, plural forms, or locations. In that case, one JSON entry can overwrite another and the importer will apply the same translation to multiple distinct messages, producing incorrect localized UI. Include a stable per-message discriminator in both export and import, such as `\u003ccomment\u003e`/`\u003cextracomment\u003e` or an exported ordinal, and match on that full key.\n```suggestion\n# Include message.findtext(\u0027comment\u0027) or a document-order id in parse/export,\n# then key translations with (context, source, comment_or_id) instead of only\n# (context, source).\n```",
